Baby, what about
your documentary?

14:52.733 --> 14:56.167
I stopped at the library
and got the grant forms.

14:56.234 --> 14:58.534
It's what
we've talked about.

14:58.600 --> 14:59.967
It's what
you've always wanted.

15:00.034 --> 15:02.568
And i'll still want it
a year from now.

15:02.633 --> 15:04.667
But this is good money,
quinn.

15:04.733 --> 15:06.700
I want to get you
a house...

15:06.767 --> 15:08.468
And that darkroom.

15:08.534 --> 15:11.700
I don't need those things.

15:11.767 --> 15:16.367
I need you to be happy
and inspired.

15:16.434 --> 15:18.334
<i>well,
this will make me happy.</i>

15:18.401 --> 15:20.667
<i>and you'll
keep me inspired.</i>

15:20.733 --> 15:22.234
[ chuckles ]

15:23.600 --> 15:24.534
Please?

15:24.600 --> 15:26.834
Say it's okay?

15:26.900 --> 15:30.667
Say, "okay."
okay, okay,
okay, okay, okay.

15:30.733 --> 15:33.067
Promise me
you'll fill out the forms.

15:33.134 --> 15:35.101
Of course.
and if something comes up,
then, that you'll take it.

15:35.167 --> 15:36.667
Of course, of course,
of course, of course.

15:36.733 --> 15:37.700
I promise.

15:37.767 --> 15:39.134
Okay.

15:42.301 --> 15:44.134
I love you,
you know that?

15:44.201 --> 15:46.600
I love you, too.

15:46.667 --> 15:49.434
Dan:
falling in love is easy.

15:49.501 --> 15:53.700
But a lifetime of love --
now, there's a miracle.

15:53.767 --> 15:55.733
You know i love you.

15:55.800 --> 15:57.201
And you know i fired alex,

15:57.267 --> 15:59.034
But you're still working
with her.

15:59.101 --> 16:02.367
I like her script, brooke.

16:02.434 --> 16:04.434
<i>you like her script
or you like her?</i>

16:06.468 --> 16:08.501
Relationships
aren't always easy.

16:08.568 --> 16:12.367
I should know.
i'm on my second marriage.

16:12.434 --> 16:14.367
[ light laughter ]
yep.

16:14.434 --> 16:16.534
How many of you
are divorced?

16:18.267 --> 16:21.401
<i>divorce doesn't just happen.</i>

16:21.468 --> 16:24.367
<i>and relationships
don't just end in an instant.</i>

16:24.434 --> 16:27.367
What'd you do with your ring,
anyway?

16:29.367 --> 16:31.434
Your wedding band.

16:31.501 --> 16:32.967
Where is it?

16:34.468 --> 16:36.767
I don't know.

16:36.834 --> 16:39.633
You don't know,
or you don't want to remember?

16:41.900 --> 16:43.534
Hey, sara...

16:43.600 --> 16:44.900
What do you think?

16:46.934 --> 16:48.900
I think you look like a boy
playing dress-up.

16:48.967 --> 16:51.633
[ sighs ] come on.
this is my shot.

16:51.700 --> 16:54.334
I got to get in the mailroom,
i become an assistant,

16:54.401 --> 16:56.067
They make me junior agent,

16:56.134 --> 16:57.733
And i'm in.
and you're in.

16:57.800 --> 16:59.800
Help.

16:59.867 --> 17:02.167
The person interviewing you --
it's a woman, right?

17:02.234 --> 17:03.600
[ sighs ] yeah.

17:03.667 --> 17:07.334
Jeans
and a button-up shirt,

17:07.401 --> 17:10.334
<i>and go heavy
on the boyish grin.</i>

17:10.401 --> 17:11.733
You sure?

17:11.800 --> 17:13.334
Hey, it got you me,
didn't it?

17:15.633 --> 17:17.434
You don't think
that will be too casual?

17:29.733 --> 17:30.900
Here.

17:33.267 --> 17:38.134
Married says mature,
stable, and dependable --

17:38.201 --> 17:40.633
Everything they'll want to see
in a future agent.

17:40.700 --> 17:42.700
Only i'm not married.

17:44.534 --> 17:47.367
Then marry me,
you knucklehead.

17:49.767 --> 17:50.867
Yes.

17:50.934 --> 17:52.234
[ laughs ]

17:52.301 --> 17:53.468
Yes!

17:53.534 --> 17:55.301
Well,
there's that boyish grin!

17:55.367 --> 17:57.834
[ giggling ]

17:57.900 --> 18:01.867
We all want to be loved,
to be happy.

18:01.934 --> 18:04.234
So why aren't we?

18:04.301 --> 18:05.867
Because we've become experts

18:05.934 --> 18:07.733
At sabotaging
our own happiness...

18:10.367 --> 18:12.633
...feeling like victims,
when, in fact,

18:12.700 --> 18:14.167
It's the choices we make.

18:14.234 --> 18:15.967
The bad habits, the vices,

18:16.034 --> 18:18.800
The inability to show love
and compassion --

18:18.867 --> 18:21.367
These are the things
that tear us down.

18:21.434 --> 18:23.134
We're not...

18:23.201 --> 18:26.034
Victims.

18:26.101 --> 18:29.334
We're assassins when it comes
to love and happiness.

18:31.667 --> 18:32.934
Renee is beautiful,

18:33.000 --> 18:36.434
And she's smart,
and she wants love in her life,

18:36.501 --> 18:39.501
And yet who did she choose
to sleep with?

18:39.568 --> 18:42.000
Allegedly.

18:42.067 --> 18:44.501
A man who was unavailable
to her.

18:46.334 --> 18:50.101
Now, she may be telling
the truth...

18:50.167 --> 18:52.201
And she may deserve
compensation,

18:52.267 --> 18:53.600
But she is no victim.

18:53.667 --> 18:57.600
[ applause ]

18:57.667 --> 18:59.600
Oh.

18:59.667 --> 19:02.667
We applaud the sentiment,
but we don't change.

19:02.733 --> 19:04.633
Why?

19:04.700 --> 19:06.301
Because we want
what we want.

19:06.367 --> 19:08.034
So we do it, we say it,
try it,

19:08.101 --> 19:10.201
And we victimize ourselves,
and we hire an attorney,

19:10.267 --> 19:11.834
And it has to stop.

19:11.900 --> 19:15.401
<i>[ applause ]</i>

19:15.468 --> 19:17.633
Renee...

19:17.700 --> 19:19.468
You say nathan scott,

19:19.534 --> 19:22.834
My son, is the father
of your unborn child, right?

19:22.900 --> 19:24.934
Yes.

19:25.000 --> 19:27.267
I believe you.

19:27.334 --> 19:29.800
<i>[ audience murmurs ]</i>

19:32.667 --> 19:34.534
<i>i think
you're telling the truth.</i>

19:34.600 --> 19:39.034
And more than that,
i'm going to prove it...

19:39.101 --> 19:42.900
With the help of
this lie-detector machine...

19:42.967 --> 19:43.967
[ audience murmurs ]

19:45.900 --> 19:48.534
...when we come back.

19:48.600 --> 19:53.000
[ applause ]

19:55.000 --> 19:58.434
This is just --

19:58.501 --> 20:00.401
This is unbelievable.

20:02.101 --> 20:04.367
[ sighs ]

20:14.301 --> 20:15.633
Two minutes, guys.

20:15.700 --> 20:17.468
What is this about?

20:17.534 --> 20:19.301
What's what about, honey?

20:19.367 --> 20:21.067
No, i-i didn't
agree to this.

20:21.134 --> 20:22.767
Relax.
it's great television.

20:22.834 --> 20:24.201
No, you don't --
here's the thing --

20:24.267 --> 20:27.501
If you're lying, science
will prove it eventually,

20:27.568 --> 20:30.434
And if not, you have nothing
to worry about.

20:30.501 --> 20:32.034
Don't forget to smile.

20:32.101 --> 20:35.767
[ footsteps departing ]
[ sighs ]

20:37.000 --> 20:38.167
Nathan.

20:38.234 --> 20:39.434
Do you believe this?

20:39.501 --> 20:41.568
Do you realize how ridiculous
this is?

20:41.633 --> 20:44.201
The guy shot his brother
at point-blank range,

20:44.267 --> 20:45.900
And now he has
a hit tv show.

20:45.967 --> 20:48.434
He's rolling out some rigged-up
lie-detector machine,

20:48.501 --> 20:51.201
And i have to sit 3,000 miles
away and just take it.

20:51.267 --> 20:52.700
Screw him.

20:52.767 --> 20:54.134
I mean it.

20:54.201 --> 20:57.134
Let's not even watch
the rest of the show.

20:57.201 --> 20:59.468
It's a nice day.

20:59.534 --> 21:00.967
It's a nice life.

21:01.034 --> 21:02.301
[ scoffs ]

21:04.501 --> 21:06.434
How can you be so strong?

21:06.501 --> 21:09.034
Dan: it's a question
of character.

21:09.101 --> 21:12.468
It's really about
who has better character.

21:12.534 --> 21:14.700
Is it renee...

21:14.767 --> 21:16.568
<i>or nathan?</i>

21:16.633 --> 21:18.800
Clay:
and if you sign with me,

21:18.867 --> 21:21.501
I promise you
that the energy and resources

21:21.568 --> 21:23.468
That i'll dedicate to you
and your career

21:23.534 --> 21:25.600
Will be unmatched.

21:25.667 --> 21:28.267
Okay. i'm in!

21:30.234 --> 21:33.000
Can i give you
my two cents?
sure.

21:33.067 --> 21:35.568
This is all still about
that wide receiver, right?

21:35.633 --> 21:36.834
Yeah.

21:38.834 --> 21:41.101
I think...

21:44.667 --> 21:46.367
...you can do better.

21:46.434 --> 21:47.867
Babe,
this guy is a big deal.

21:47.934 --> 21:49.700
I mean, he can change
everything for me.

21:49.767 --> 21:52.167
But you said it yourself --
he's a bad guy.

21:52.234 --> 21:53.667
And if i only represent
good guys,

21:53.733 --> 21:55.067
I may have no clients
at all.

21:55.134 --> 21:57.733
No, i don't believe that.
i don't think you do, either.

21:57.800 --> 21:59.534
The guy is great, sara.

21:59.600 --> 22:03.201
<i>he's not great.
he's just a great player.</i>

22:03.267 --> 22:05.867
And the man i love
knows the difference.

22:05.934 --> 22:09.967
That's what's gonna make you
a great agent.

22:10.034 --> 22:12.733
You'll find players
that you can believe in

22:12.800 --> 22:15.733
And clients
that become friends.

22:15.800 --> 22:17.034
You'll find someone

22:17.101 --> 22:20.800
Who has integrity
and character and heart.

22:20.867 --> 22:23.568
<i>and that will change everything
for you.</i>

22:26.101 --> 22:30.101
<i>and that's the man
i fell in love with.</i>

22:30.167 --> 22:32.201
[ both chuckle ]

22:32.267 --> 22:33.600
Brooke: i love you,
you know that.

22:33.667 --> 22:34.867
I know.

22:36.568 --> 22:37.867
[ sighs ]

22:37.934 --> 22:39.034
You really hurt
my feelings

22:39.101 --> 22:40.568
When you said
we weren't getting married.

22:40.633 --> 22:42.967
When did i ever say anything
about marriage?

22:43.034 --> 22:44.667
When your dad
came to town.

22:44.733 --> 22:46.867
You said
we weren't getting married

22:46.934 --> 22:49.967
Like it was some sort of
completely ridiculous notion

22:50.034 --> 22:51.067
To you.

22:51.134 --> 22:52.167
No.

22:52.234 --> 22:53.201
Brooke, i was venting.

22:53.267 --> 22:54.468
It had nothing to do

22:54.534 --> 22:56.167
With the actual concept
of marrying you.

22:58.134 --> 23:00.301
I think about that
all the time.

23:00.367 --> 23:02.633
Really?

23:02.700 --> 23:04.568
Yeah.

23:06.067 --> 23:09.167
Well, good, because that's what
i wrote in the sand.

23:10.800 --> 23:13.167
That night you said
you were gonna take that
movie in new zealand,

23:13.234 --> 23:15.667
I-i wrote "marry me"
in the sand,

23:15.733 --> 23:17.134
And then
i didn't tell you

23:17.201 --> 23:18.800
Because you said
you were leaving.

23:20.800 --> 23:22.633
Surprise.

23:22.700 --> 23:24.401
Quinn: david?

23:27.934 --> 23:29.434
David.

23:33.767 --> 23:35.867
What is this?

23:35.934 --> 23:38.101
Surprise.

23:38.167 --> 23:39.501
Dan:
i know this is a surprise,

23:39.568 --> 23:41.134
But we have an expression
on this show --

23:41.201 --> 23:42.468
Step into the light...

23:42.534 --> 23:44.468
Together:
and get yourself right!

23:44.534 --> 23:46.000
...and get yourself right.

23:46.067 --> 23:47.201
During the break,

23:47.267 --> 23:48.700
We hooked renee up
to a lie detector,

23:48.767 --> 23:50.201
And here's how it works.

23:50.267 --> 23:53.101
I'll ask renee a question,
and depending on her answer,

23:53.167 --> 23:55.101
The words "true" or "lie"

23:55.167 --> 23:57.468
Will appear on the screens
behind me.

23:57.534 --> 24:00.101
For instance,
is your name renee richardson?

24:00.167 --> 24:01.101
Yes.

24:03.434 --> 24:04.934
Excellent.
let's begin.

24:05.000 --> 24:07.900
Did you, in fact,
meet nathan scott at a party,

24:07.967 --> 24:09.534
As you described earlier?

24:09.600 --> 24:10.834
Yes.

24:13.401 --> 24:15.034
<i>did you flirt
with nathan scott?</i>

24:15.101 --> 24:16.733
Yes.

24:18.434 --> 24:20.367
Did nathan flirt back?

24:20.434 --> 24:22.134
Renee:
you smell good.

24:22.201 --> 24:24.167
That's my rainstorm
body spray.

24:24.234 --> 24:25.401
Oh.

24:25.468 --> 24:26.800
Yes.

24:26.867 --> 24:28.334
[ audience murmurs ]

24:28.401 --> 24:33.101
Believe only what you yourself
test and judge to be true.

24:33.167 --> 24:36.867
Renee,
is nathan scott, my son,

24:36.934 --> 24:38.834
The father
of your unborn child?

24:46.934 --> 24:49.000
Yes.

24:51.134 --> 24:52.234
[ audience gasps ]

25:05.235 --> 25:06.235
Hey, it's Clay.

25:06.235 --> 25:08.234
It's my third time calling,
buddy.

25:08.301 --> 25:10.000
Look, i'm watching the show
right now,

25:10.067 --> 25:12.800
And i, um...i just want
to talk to you.

25:12.867 --> 25:14.800
So, please call me back,
all right?

25:17.967 --> 25:20.067
Hales?

25:20.134 --> 25:21.467
Nathan?

25:24.601 --> 25:27.900
* i won't do what you told me *

25:27.967 --> 25:29.900
* i won't do what you said *

25:29.967 --> 25:33.234
* no, i'm not
gonna stop feeling *

25:33.301 --> 25:35.833
* i'm not gonna forget *

25:35.900 --> 25:37.800
Hey, david,
do you know where --

25:37.867 --> 25:39.134
Hey, babe.

25:39.200 --> 25:42.567
Uh...what is this?

25:42.634 --> 25:46.734
Okay, okay,
i-i know it's expensive,

25:46.800 --> 25:48.800
But i just had
a thought --

25:48.867 --> 25:50.234
Screening room.

25:50.301 --> 25:52.434
Okay.
i'm just saying --

25:52.501 --> 25:55.967
I go to work, i come home,
i sit here --

25:56.034 --> 25:58.067
I'm happy.

26:02.401 --> 26:05.134
Remember that old car
that we had...

26:05.200 --> 26:06.367
And the futon?

26:08.601 --> 26:10.534
We were really happy then.

26:10.601 --> 26:12.067
Yeah,
that futon sucked, baby.

26:16.501 --> 26:18.267
I love this picture
of you.

26:19.534 --> 26:20.867
Really?

26:20.933 --> 26:24.234
'cause that guy was struggling,
foolish, and broke.

26:24.301 --> 26:25.933
That's not true.
quinn...

26:28.167 --> 26:30.567
...you've got some crazy,
romantic notion

26:30.634 --> 26:33.100
<i>of who i used to be,
of who we used to be.</i>

26:33.167 --> 26:35.534
We were just naive kids.

26:35.601 --> 26:37.967
God forbid
i ever go back to that.

26:38.034 --> 26:39.734
Can you hand me
a phillips screwdriver?

26:39.800 --> 26:41.467
It's in the box
over there.

26:41.534 --> 26:43.367
Sure.

26:43.434 --> 26:45.967
How great is this room,
by the way?

26:46.034 --> 26:47.900
No windows.
it's perfect.

26:51.034 --> 26:52.768
It's a really dark room.

26:54.833 --> 26:57.800
Did you mean it
when you proposed?

26:59.200 --> 27:00.933
I did that night.

27:01.000 --> 27:02.800
But not anymore.

27:02.867 --> 27:05.100
I don't know right now.

27:09.167 --> 27:11.334
I'm sorry.

27:11.401 --> 27:12.800
I didn't know.

27:18.833 --> 27:20.634
I'm sorry
i hurt your feelings.

27:24.367 --> 27:26.301
[ sighs ]

27:26.367 --> 27:29.367
Dan: sometimes we fall short of
the people we are meant to be,

27:29.434 --> 27:32.301
And sometimes people do things
they're ashamed of.

27:33.234 --> 27:34.967
Thank you, renee.

27:35.034 --> 27:37.501
And usually,
after the guilt sets in,

27:37.567 --> 27:39.200
We make things worse.

27:41.167 --> 27:43.668
My son, nathan scott,
is a good man,

27:43.734 --> 27:46.100
But sometimes people
do funny things

27:46.167 --> 27:48.534
In the face of pressure
and desperation.

27:48.601 --> 27:50.200
And the truth...

27:50.267 --> 27:54.634
Well,
truth is an absolute,

27:54.701 --> 27:56.601
And the truth
can set you free.

27:58.867 --> 28:00.501
My name is dan scott.

28:03.367 --> 28:05.701
I love my wife, rachel.

28:08.800 --> 28:10.534
What is he doing?

28:10.601 --> 28:12.334
My son, nathan, loves me.

28:16.467 --> 28:18.567
I'm president
of the united states.

28:18.634 --> 28:20.467
[ light laughter ]

28:20.534 --> 28:22.867
[ audience murmurs ]

28:22.933 --> 28:24.367
I'm santa claus.

28:25.867 --> 28:26.768
[ audience murmurs ]

28:26.833 --> 28:29.134
I didn't kill my brother.

28:30.900 --> 28:32.933
[ audience "oohs" ]

28:33.000 --> 28:35.734
Hey, you guys
got to get in here!

28:37.134 --> 28:38.434
Life is funny, isn't it?

28:40.501 --> 28:43.134
Sometimes bad things
happen to good people,

28:43.200 --> 28:45.567
And it isn't fair.

28:45.634 --> 28:47.601
This is a still frame
of the moment i told you

28:47.668 --> 28:49.534
We were gonna do
the lie-detector test.

28:49.601 --> 28:52.900
Your pupils are dilated.
your eyebrows are arched.

28:52.967 --> 28:54.301
It means
you were surprised.

28:57.067 --> 28:59.167
This is a still frame
of the moment

28:59.234 --> 29:01.534
After you said nathan
had slept with you

29:01.601 --> 29:04.000
And the monitors
said "true."

29:04.067 --> 29:05.734
You were surprised again,
weren't you?

29:10.634 --> 29:13.200
Sometimes bad things happen
to good people.

29:14.800 --> 29:16.501
I think you're a good person,
renee.

29:16.567 --> 29:18.367
I think something bad
happened to you,

29:18.434 --> 29:19.867
And you were clever enough
to see a way out.

29:19.933 --> 29:21.267
Nathan: all right.

29:21.334 --> 29:23.867
[ chuckles ] mmm.
you smell good.

29:23.933 --> 29:26.067
Oh, that's the rainstorm
body spray. [ chuckles ]

29:26.134 --> 29:28.367
All right.
let's make it look sexy.

29:28.434 --> 29:30.167
Okay -- ooh, easy.

29:30.234 --> 29:31.467
<i>not too sexy.</i>

29:31.534 --> 29:33.601
That'll cost us $20 million
next year.

29:33.668 --> 29:36.401
On the count of 2.
1...2.

29:37.867 --> 29:39.701
I don't think
you wanted to.

29:39.768 --> 29:42.933
I think you were afraid...
and lost and desperate.

29:45.000 --> 29:46.800
You knew nathan
was in a contract year,

29:46.867 --> 29:48.967
And you knew he had
too much to drink that night.

29:53.067 --> 29:55.100
Maybe someone lied
to you,

29:55.167 --> 29:58.134
Maybe someone took advantage
of you, or maybe...

29:58.200 --> 30:00.167
Being a good person
just wasn't paying off.

30:03.668 --> 30:05.800
I don't want
to do this anymore.

30:05.867 --> 30:08.833
I know.
but here's the good news.

30:11.334 --> 30:13.067
You can stop it --

30:13.134 --> 30:16.800
Right here, right now.

30:16.867 --> 30:19.768
You wanted to get some money,
some security.

30:19.833 --> 30:22.967
What's so little
to someone who has so much?

30:23.034 --> 30:26.833
And then you got angry,
and then the press got involved,

30:26.900 --> 30:28.167
And then there was
no turning back.

30:30.100 --> 30:31.833
Renee...

30:31.900 --> 30:35.000
We have a team
of experts backstage

30:35.067 --> 30:37.167
Who study body language
and heart-rate response

30:37.234 --> 30:38.367
And all of it.

30:40.833 --> 30:42.234
You were at that party
that night,

30:42.301 --> 30:43.434
And you had sex,
didn't you?

30:46.668 --> 30:48.401
And you got pregnant.

30:51.634 --> 30:54.100
But you didn't have sex
with nathan scott,

30:54.167 --> 30:56.833
<i>and you never had sex
with nathan scott, did you?</i>

31:02.867 --> 31:04.634
No.

31:07.000 --> 31:08.800
[ sobs ]

31:15.467 --> 31:16.967
[ sighs ]

31:19.534 --> 31:22.334
Well, what do you know?

31:22.401 --> 31:26.534
Character
changes everything.

31:26.601 --> 31:29.601
It's okay.

31:29.668 --> 31:31.267
It's okay.

31:31.334 --> 31:33.334
It's over now.

31:45.367 --> 31:47.267
It's okay.
[ sobs ]

31:47.334 --> 31:49.334
It's over.

31:54.667 --> 31:55.734
Thanks.

31:58.067 --> 31:59.801
He says she's dropping
everything.

31:59.868 --> 32:01.634
[ sighs ]

32:05.634 --> 32:08.767
I'm so sorry
you had to go through this.

32:08.834 --> 32:10.634
I shouldn't have been drunk
at that party, haley.

32:10.701 --> 32:11.734
I just --

32:11.801 --> 32:13.667
You --

32:13.734 --> 32:15.834
You're still young.

32:15.901 --> 32:17.434
We both are.

32:17.501 --> 32:19.701
I think --

32:19.767 --> 32:22.400
I think we just forget
that sometimes.

32:22.467 --> 32:23.567
[ chuckles softly ]

32:30.234 --> 32:31.767
[ sighs ]

32:39.901 --> 32:42.434
What are you
listening to?

32:42.501 --> 32:44.234
You know.

32:44.300 --> 32:47.300
I never changed it.

32:47.367 --> 32:48.801
Play it.

32:50.634 --> 32:52.300
I can't.

32:52.367 --> 32:54.200
For me?

33:10.467 --> 33:14.234
[ willie nelson's "angel flying
too close to the ground" plays ]

33:14.300 --> 33:17.133
* if you had not have
fallen... *

33:20.567 --> 33:22.400
I love this song.

33:24.534 --> 33:25.834
You look beautiful.

33:25.901 --> 33:27.868
Well, thank you,
handsome.

33:27.934 --> 33:29.267
Dance with me.

33:38.067 --> 33:41.067
* and i patched up
your broken wing *

33:45.901 --> 33:48.200
You know what i want?

33:48.267 --> 33:50.767
What?

33:50.834 --> 33:52.534
Grape kool-aid.

33:52.601 --> 33:54.234
* trying to keep
your spirits up *

33:54.300 --> 33:57.400
[ laughs ]

33:57.467 --> 34:00.968
* and your fever down *

34:01.033 --> 34:02.667
[ chuckling ]

34:05.167 --> 34:09.501
* i knew someday... *

34:09.567 --> 34:11.067
You know what i hate?

34:11.132 --> 34:12.234
I hate these pens.

34:12.300 --> 34:13.900
It's either
way too much fluid

34:13.967 --> 34:15.100
Or not nearly enough,

34:15.167 --> 34:16.801
But it's never
the right amount.

34:16.868 --> 34:19.234
And they cost,
like, a fortune.

34:19.300 --> 34:20.766
[ page turns ]

34:20.833 --> 34:23.501
What are you looking at,
you goof?

34:24.634 --> 34:25.833
Sara, hey.

34:25.900 --> 34:27.400
Hey, sara! hey!

34:34.467 --> 34:39.234
* so leave me if you need to *

34:41.934 --> 34:45.467
* i will still remember *

34:48.701 --> 34:54.199
* angel flying too close *

34:54.266 --> 34:58.534
* to the ground *

35:02.234 --> 35:06.901
* leave me if you need to *

35:09.567 --> 35:13.501
* i will still remember *

35:16.934 --> 35:22.701
* angel flying too close *

35:22.767 --> 35:27.000
* to the ground *

35:30.267 --> 35:33.067
[ cheers and applause ]

35:35.701 --> 35:37.367
[ record crackling ]

35:37.434 --> 35:39.133
[ knock on door ]

35:39.200 --> 35:40.167
[ echoing ] clay.

35:42.501 --> 35:44.734
[ breathing shakily ]

35:44.801 --> 35:47.534
Sometimes
i can't see you anymore.

35:52.200 --> 35:54.367
I forget things about you,

35:54.434 --> 35:57.167
And i'm afraid
that i'm losing us.

35:58.601 --> 36:01.534
Like the way you smelled
and, uh...

36:01.601 --> 36:04.367
The sound of your voice
and how you felt in my arms,

36:04.434 --> 36:05.767
And, um...

36:05.834 --> 36:08.701
If you let someone in,
you'll erase me.

36:08.767 --> 36:10.400
You won't.

36:10.467 --> 36:13.000
I can't.

36:13.067 --> 36:14.767
[ knock on door ]

36:17.300 --> 36:19.367
Open the door, clay.

36:19.434 --> 36:22.133
[ sighs ]

36:22.200 --> 36:23.667
Clay...

36:23.734 --> 36:25.367
It's okay.

36:25.434 --> 36:27.734
On the count of 2.

36:37.667 --> 36:41.801
1...2.

36:43.400 --> 36:45.067
Hey!

36:49.200 --> 36:50.834
I think
you need to go home.

36:50.901 --> 36:53.534
Oh, okay. i'm sorry.
i didn't know it was a bad time.

36:53.601 --> 36:55.100
To david.

36:55.167 --> 36:56.834
I think you should go home
to david.

36:58.400 --> 37:01.267
And i'm sorry, too.

37:01.334 --> 37:04.801
* load the car
and write the note *

37:07.567 --> 37:10.834
* grab your bag
and grab your coat *

37:10.901 --> 37:13.567
I love you so much,
my beautiful wife.

37:13.634 --> 37:17.968
[ sighs ]
* tell the ones
that need to know *

37:19.767 --> 37:22.100
* we are headed north *

37:24.601 --> 37:28.534
* one foot in, one foot back *

37:30.567 --> 37:34.501
* but it don't pay to live
like that *

37:36.067 --> 37:40.501
* so i cut the tires,
and i jump the tracks *

37:42.067 --> 37:45.534
* for never to return *

37:47.968 --> 37:52.234
* ah, brooklyn, brooklyn,
take me in *

37:52.800 --> 37:56.401
"a team
of experts backstage"?

37:57.600 --> 38:00.034
Nice touch.

38:00.101 --> 38:03.067
So how'd you know
she was lying?

38:05.667 --> 38:07.700
He's still my son.
i raised him.

38:07.767 --> 38:10.434
I know what kind of man
he is.

38:10.500 --> 38:11.867
Besides...

38:11.934 --> 38:15.201
Takes a con
to know a con.

38:15.267 --> 38:17.034
It was a good show.

38:18.567 --> 38:20.134
I love you.

38:22.334 --> 38:23.967
Yeah.

38:27.401 --> 38:33.101
* with him and her
and you and me *

38:33.167 --> 38:38.234
* ah, but it's just
a waste of time *

38:38.301 --> 38:41.567
* yeah,
it's such a waste of time *

38:41.633 --> 38:43.600
You okay?

38:43.667 --> 38:46.001
No.

38:47.633 --> 38:51.067
I need to know that you feel
the same way that i do,

38:51.134 --> 38:55.401
That you can...see yourself
doing this with me forever,

38:55.468 --> 38:56.967
Because if not,
what am i doing?

38:57.034 --> 38:59.401
<i>what -- what are we doing?
what --</i>

38:59.468 --> 39:00.734
Hey.
who are we?

39:00.800 --> 39:03.134
Hey. look at me.

39:05.067 --> 39:07.934
<i>we're us, brooke.</i>

39:08.001 --> 39:12.267
You're the girl i love
with all my heart,

39:12.334 --> 39:15.434
And i'm the boy who's gonna be
with you forever.

39:17.934 --> 39:20.734
We don't have to rush
into anything.

39:20.800 --> 39:22.800
Forever is
a very long time.

39:25.167 --> 39:29.134
* ah, brooklyn, brooklyn,
take me in *

39:42.067 --> 39:45.234
It's not fair.

39:45.301 --> 39:48.267
We were supposed
to have more time.

39:48.334 --> 39:50.600
<i>and you still do.</i>

39:50.667 --> 39:53.034
I don't want you
to be alone, honey.

39:53.101 --> 39:56.067
You like her -- quinn.

39:56.134 --> 39:58.401
Why'd you send her away?

40:01.567 --> 40:03.867
I don't want to lose us.

40:03.934 --> 40:07.967
No, you can't erase who we were
or what we had.

40:08.034 --> 40:09.434
No one can.

40:11.301 --> 40:13.934
We burned
so bright together.

40:15.267 --> 40:17.267
You won't lose that.

40:17.334 --> 40:20.167
I loved you so much, sara.

40:20.234 --> 40:23.700
You were perfect with me...

40:23.767 --> 40:25.767
And you always will be.

40:28.434 --> 40:31.201
But now it's time
to let go.

40:33.468 --> 40:35.967
It's okay, honey.

40:37.368 --> 40:42.034
* are you aware of the shape
i'm in? *

40:42.101 --> 40:44.101
I love you.

40:44.167 --> 40:47.767
* my hands, they shake,
my head, it spins *

40:47.834 --> 40:49.500
* spins *

40:49.567 --> 40:54.500
* ah, brooklyn, brooklyn,
take me in *

40:54.567 --> 41:00.767
* dumbed down
and numbed by time and age *

41:00.834 --> 41:07.001
* your dreams that catch
the world the cage *

41:07.067 --> 41:12.301
* the highway sets
the traveler's stage *

41:12.368 --> 41:15.967
* all exits look the same *

41:18.267 --> 41:22.434
* three words
that became hard to say *

41:24.900 --> 41:30.401
* "i" and "love" and "you" *

